.TH ISSY 1 "April 17, 2026" "issy 1.0.0" "General Commands Manual"
.SH NAME
issy \- a text editor that looks like a printed page
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B issy
.RB [ \-\-version ]
.RB [ \-\-help ]
.RB [ \-\-no\-config ]
.RB [ \-\-config
.IR file ]
.RB [ \-\-theme
.IR name ]
.RB [ \-\-font
.IR path ]
.RB [ \-\-print
.IR output ]
.RB [ \-\-rollback ]
.RI [ file\fR[\fB:\fIline\fR]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B issy
is a text editor written in Zig with zero external dependencies.
It renders a single buffer in a terminal using gap-buffer text storage,
syntax highlighting, undo/redo, incremental search, search and replace,
multi-cursor editing, keyboard and mouse selection, bracket matching,
and PDF export with real TTF/OTF font embedding.
.PP
The visual design is deliberately restrained: only two or three token
types get real chromatic contrast; the eye parses structure through
gentle luminance shifts rather than a full-spectrum rainbow.
Two built-in themes are provided:
.B default
(dark) and
.B paper
(Solarized Light).
.PP
.B issy
requires a terminal.
Standard input must be a tty; if it is not,
.B issy
prints a diagnostic to standard error and exits with status 1.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-version ", " \-v
Print version string and exit.
The output includes the version number, abbreviated commit SHA, and
build type
.RB ( release
or
.BR dev ).
.TP
.BR \-\-help ", " \-h
Print a usage summary and exit.
.TP
.BI \-\-config " file"
Read configuration from
.I file
instead of the default
.IR ~/.issyrc .
.TP
.BI \-\-theme " name"
Override the theme.
.I name
is one of
.B default
or
.BR paper .
.TP
.BI \-\-font " path"
Use
.I path
as the TTF or OTF font for PDF output.
Overrides the
.B font_file
setting in the configuration file.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-config
Skip loading any configuration file.
All settings take their compiled-in defaults.
.TP
.BI \-\-print " output"
Export the file to PDF at
.I output
and exit without opening the TUI.
Requires a font, either via
.B \-\-font
or
.B font_file
in the configuration file.
A file argument must also be provided.
.TP
.B \-\-rollback
Replace the running binary on disk with the snapshot taken before the
last successful auto-update apply
.RI ( ~/.cache/issy/issy.prev ),
then exit.
Prints an error and exits with status 1 if no snapshot exists or the
binary is not writable.
.SH KEYBINDINGS
In normal mode the following key sequences are recognized.
Multi-byte input is handled as UTF-8.
.SS Editing
.TP
.B Ctrl+S
Save the current buffer.
If the buffer has no filename, the status bar shows an error; use
.B Ctrl+O
to open or name a file first.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Q
Quit.
If the buffer has unsaved changes, the status bar prompts for
confirmation; press
.B Ctrl+Q
again to discard changes and exit.
.TP
.B Ctrl+W
Same as
.BR Ctrl+Q .
.TP
.B Ctrl+Z
Undo the last editing operation.
Multi-cursor edits are undone as a single atomic step.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Y
Redo.
.TP
.B Ctrl+C
Copy the current selection to the internal clipboard.
.TP
.B Ctrl+X
Cut the current selection.
.TP
.B Ctrl+V
Paste from the internal clipboard.
With multiple cursors active, the paste is applied at every cursor.
.TP
.B Ctrl+A
Select all text in the buffer.
.TP
.B Tab
Insert a tab character or the equivalent number of spaces,
depending on the
.B expand_tabs
and
.B tab_width
settings.
If the file's indentation style was auto-detected, the detected style
takes precedence.
.TP
.B Enter
Insert a newline.
If
.B auto_indent
is enabled, the new line copies the leading whitespace of the
preceding line.
.TP
.B Backspace
Delete the character before the cursor.
If a selection is active, delete the selected text instead.
.TP
.B Delete
Delete the character under the cursor.
If a selection is active, delete the selected text instead.
.SS Cursor movement
.TP
.B Arrow keys
Move the cursor one character or one line.
Clears any active selection.
.TP
.BR Ctrl+Left ", " Ctrl+Right
Jump the cursor one word boundary at a time.
Clears any active selection.
.TP
.B Home
Move to the beginning of the current line.
Clears any active selection.
.TP
.B End
Move to the end of the current line.
Clears any active selection.
.TP
.BR "Page Up" ", " "Page Down"
Move the cursor by one screenfull minus two lines.
.SS Selection
Selection extends a highlighted region from an anchor point to the
cursor.
The anchor is set when the first shift-modified movement key is pressed
or when the mouse initiates a drag.
.TP
.BR Shift+Up ", " Shift+Down ", " Shift+Left ", " Shift+Right
Extend the selection by one character or one line.
.TP
.BR Ctrl+Shift+Left ", " Ctrl+Shift+Right
Extend the selection by one word.
.TP
.B Shift+Home
Extend the selection to the beginning of the current line.
.TP
.B Shift+End
Extend the selection to the end of the current line.
.TP
.B Escape
Clear the selection and all extra cursors.
.SS Search and replace
.TP
.B Ctrl+F
Enter incremental search mode.
Each keystroke re-runs the search and jumps the cursor to the first
match.
Press
.B Enter
to confirm the cursor position, or
.B Escape
to cancel and return the cursor to where it was before the search
began.
.TP
.B Ctrl+G
Jump to the next occurrence of the last search pattern.
Works in both normal mode and search mode.
.TP
.B Ctrl+H
Enter search-and-replace mode.
Type the search pattern, press
.B Tab
to switch to the replacement field (press
.B Tab
again to switch back), then:
.RS
.TP
.B Enter
Replace the current match and advance to the next.
.TP
.B Ctrl+A
Replace all occurrences and return to normal mode.
.TP
.B Escape
Cancel and return to normal mode.
.RE
.SS Files and buffers
.TP
.B Ctrl+O
Open a file.
The prompt is seeded with the current working directory.
Type a partial path and press
.B Tab
to complete against the filesystem.
Press
.B Escape
to cancel.
.TP
.B Ctrl+N
Open a new empty buffer.
If the current buffer has unsaved changes, the editor prompts for
confirmation first.
.TP
.B Ctrl+P
Export the current buffer to a PDF file alongside the source file
(same directory,
.I .pdf
suffix).
Requires the buffer to have a filename and a font to be configured via
.B font_file
or
.BR \-\-font .
.TP
.B Ctrl+R
Reload the file from disk.
Only takes effect when
.B issy
has detected that the file's modification time has changed since it was
last read.
The file's mtime is polled once per second.
.SS Multi-cursor
.TP
.B Ctrl+D
Select the word under the cursor.
Press again to add an additional cursor at the next occurrence of the
same word.
Repeat to keep adding cursors.
.PP
All editing operations \(em typing, backspace, delete, paste \(em apply
to every cursor simultaneously.
.B Ctrl+Z
undoes the entire multi-cursor operation as a single step.
.B Escape
clears all extra cursors and the selection.
.SS Mouse
.TP
.B Click
Position the cursor at the click location.
Clears any selection and extra cursors.
.TP
.B Double-click
Select the word under the pointer.
.TP
.B Triple-click
Select the entire line under the pointer.
.PP
Click counting uses a 400\ ms timeout at the same buffer position;
intervening scrolling does not break the streak.
.TP
.B Shift+Click
Extend the selection from the current anchor (or from the cursor,
if no selection is active) to the click position.
.TP
.B Click and drag
Extend the selection as the pointer moves.
Dragging past the top or bottom edge of the viewport autoscrolls.
.TP
.B Mouse scroll
Scroll the viewport by three lines.
The cursor position is not changed unless it falls outside the visible
area, in which case it is clamped to the nearest visible row.
.SS Help
.TP
.BR Ctrl+/ ", " F1
Display a keybindings overlay.
Press any key to dismiss.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is read from
.I ~/.issyrc
on startup, unless
.B \-\-no\-config
is given or an alternate file is specified with
.BR \-\-config .
.PP
The file format is line-oriented.
Lines starting with
.B #
are comments.
Unknown keys are silently ignored.
Values containing spaces may be quoted with double quotes.
Theme sections are introduced with a
.BI [theme. name ]
header.
.PP
The installer seeds
.I ~/.issyrc
with every setting commented out so the available keys and their
defaults are visible.
See
.I examples/issyrc
in the source tree for a complete annotated example.
.SS Editing settings
.TP
.BR tab_width " (default: 4)"
Number of columns per tab stop.
.TP
.BR expand_tabs " (default: true)"
Insert spaces instead of literal tab characters.
.TP
.BR auto_indent " (default: true)"
Copy leading whitespace from the preceding line when pressing
.BR Enter .
.TP
.BR auto_close_brackets " (default: false)"
Automatically insert a matching closing bracket or quote after an
opening one.
.TP
.BR auto_detect_indent " (default: true)"
Scan the file on open to detect whether it uses tabs or spaces, and
the prevailing tab width.
The detected values override
.B tab_width
and
.B expand_tabs
for that file.
.TP
.BR scroll_margin " (default: 5)"
Minimum number of lines between the cursor and the top or bottom of
the viewport before the view scrolls.
.SS Display settings
.TP
.BR line_numbers " (default: true)"
Show line numbers in the gutter.
.TP
.BR left_padding " (default: 2)"
Columns of blank space before the line-number gutter.
.TP
.BR gutter_padding " (default: 3)"
Columns of blank space between the line numbers and the code.
.TP
.BR word_wrap " (default: true)"
Soft-wrap long lines at the right margin.
Continuation lines are indented.
.TP
.BR right_margin " (default: 100)"
Column at which text stops and the remaining terminal width is left
as empty background.
Set to 0 to fill the terminal.
.TP
.BR cursor_line_bg " (default: true)"
Subtly highlight the full width of the line containing the cursor.
.TP
.BR cursor_style " (default: bar)"
Terminal cursor shape.
One of
.BR bar ,
.BR block ,
or
.BR underline .
.TP
.BR trailing_whitespace " (default: true)"
Faintly highlight trailing spaces and tabs on non-empty lines.
.TP
.BR indent_mismatch " (default: true)"
Faintly highlight leading indentation that does not match the detected
or configured style for the file.
.SS Auto-update settings
.TP
.BR notify_updates " (default: true)"
On startup, check for a newer release and show
\(lqupdate available:
.IR sha \(rq
in the status bar.
Set to
.B false
to disable the check and its background network fetch entirely.
Only applies to release builds; dev builds skip the check regardless.
.TP
.BR autoupdate " (default: false)"
Opt into automatic download, Ed25519 signature verification, and
in-session re-exec when a newer release is available.
See
.B AUTO-UPDATE
below for the full mechanism.
.SS PDF settings
.TP
.B font_file
Path to a TTF or OTF font file.
Required for
.B Ctrl+P
and
.BR \-\-print .
.TP
.BR font_size " (default: 10.0)"
Font size in points for PDF output.
.TP
.BR print_margin_top " (default: 72.0)"
Top page margin in points (72\ points = 1\ inch).
.TP
.BR print_margin_bottom " (default: 72.0)"
Bottom page margin in points.
.TP
.BR print_margin_left " (default: 108.0)"
Left page margin in points.
.TP
.BR print_margin_right " (default: 72.0)"
Right page margin in points.
.SS Theme settings
Switch themes by adding a section header:
.PP
.RS
.B [theme.paper]
.RE
.PP
The only built-in themes are
.B default
(dark, active by default) and
.B paper
(Solarized Light).
.PP
Individual colors may be overridden after the section header using
.B #rrggbb
hex format.
The available color keys are:
.BR bg ,
.BR fg ,
.BR keyword ,
.BR string_color ,
.BR comment ,
.BR number_color ,
.BR type_color ,
.BR function_color ,
.BR operator_color ,
.BR preprocessor_color ,
.BR line_number_color ,
.BR line_number_active ,
.BR cursor_line_color ,
.BR selection_color ,
.BR trailing_ws_color ,
and
.BR indent_mismatch_color .
.SH SYNTAX HIGHLIGHTING
Language is detected by file extension.
The following languages are supported:
C, C++, Zig, Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, Rust, Go, Shell (sh/bash),
HTML, CSS, JSON, YAML, TOML, Makefile, Markdown, and TeX/LaTeX.
.PP
Tokenization is performed line by line using a state machine with no
allocations in the hot path.
Multi-line constructs such as block comments are tracked across lines
via persistent state.
.SH PDF EXPORT
.B Ctrl+P
exports the current buffer to a PDF\ 1.4 file alongside the source
(same directory,
.I .pdf
suffix).
.B \-\-print
does the same headlessly without opening the TUI.
Both require a TTF or OTF font file configured via
.B font_file
in the configuration or
.B \-\-font
on the command line.
.PP
PDF output uses a dedicated print theme with colors tuned for ink on
white paper; it never inherits the TUI theme.
The PDF writer is implemented entirely in Zig with no external
dependencies \(em no intermediate PostScript, no system libraries.
Output includes syntax highlighting, line numbers, a header with the
filename, and automatic page breaks.
.SH AUTO-UPDATE
Release builds (those produced by CI, not local dev builds)
check for newer versions on startup.
A detached background worker fetches
.I commit.txt
from the latest GitHub release and caches it under
.IR ~/.cache/issy/ .
The editor never blocks on the network.
If the cached commit SHA differs from the one the running binary was
built from, the status bar shows
\(lqupdate available:
.IR sha \(rq.
.PP
With
.B autoupdate = true
in the configuration, the worker additionally downloads
.I sha256sums.txt
and
.IR sha256sums.txt.sig ,
verifies the Ed25519 signature against the public key embedded at build
time
.RI ( src/update_key.zig ),
hashes the downloaded binary against the signed manifest, and stages it
at
.IR ~/.cache/issy/issy.staged .
.PP
When the buffer is clean (no unsaved changes) and the editor has been
idle for 60\ seconds, the running binary is snapshotted to
.IR issy.prev ,
the staged binary is atomically renamed into place, and the editor
re-execs itself with an internal
.B \-\-resume
flag so the new instance restores the open file at the same cursor
position.
The terminal state survives the
.BR execve (2);
the user sees at most one re-render.
.PP
Auto-apply is a no-op when:
.IP \(bu 2
The install path is owned by root (the binary is not writable by the
running user).
.IP \(bu 2
The binary is a dev build.
.IP \(bu 2
The platform has no prebuilt binary (macOS \(em see below).
.PP
On macOS,
.B issy
does not ship prebuilt binaries because cross-compiled Mach-O from
Linux lacks a code signature and is rejected by the Apple Silicon kernel.
The notify path still works; run
.B "brew upgrade \-\-fetch\-HEAD issy"
or rebuild from source to update.
.PP
Use
.B \-\-rollback
to revert after an apply, or set
.B notify_updates = false
to disable the entire mechanism.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B HOME
Used to locate the default configuration file
.RI ( $HOME/.issyrc )
and the auto-update cache directory
.RI ( $HOME/.cache/issy/ ).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.issyrc
User configuration file.
See
.BR CONFIGURATION .
.TP
.I ~/.cache/issy/
Auto-update cache directory.
Contains:
.I commit.txt
(latest release SHA),
.I sha256sums.txt
and
.I sha256sums.txt.sig
(signed manifest),
.I issy.staged
(verified binary ready for apply), and
.I issy.prev
(snapshot of the binary before the last apply, used by
.BR \-\-rollback ).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Normal exit.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred: standard input is not a terminal, PDF export failed,
or
.B \-\-rollback
failed (no snapshot or binary not writable).
.SH EXAMPLES
Open a file:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ issy main.zig
.fi
.RE
.PP
Open at a specific line:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ issy src/editor.zig:42
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start with an empty buffer:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ issy
.fi
.RE
.PP
Export to PDF headlessly:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ issy \-\-font /path/to/font.ttf \-\-print output.pdf source.c
.fi
.RE
.PP
Revert the last auto-update:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ issy \-\-rollback
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR vi (1),
.BR nano (1)
.SH AUTHORS
David Emerson
.SH CAVEATS
.B issy
uses an internal clipboard, not the system clipboard.
Copy and paste only work within the same
.B issy
session.
.PP
The
.B auto_close_brackets
feature is available but disabled by default; it can interfere with
common editing patterns in some languages.
